    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02943.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Belmont<ptr target="loc.02943_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1888-06-08" rend="right"> June 8 / 88</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt Whitman;&#8212;</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Mr Harned<ptr target="loc.03745_n1"/> has written me of <choice>
                    <abbr>yr</abbr>
                    <expan>your</expan>
                </choice> recent attack of illness. It was at first quite alarming. But thank God it
                was no worse. I wont weary you by saying more than to express my <hi
                    rend="underline">heartfelt sympathy &#38; thankfulness &#38; good wishes</hi>. I
                sent Mr Harned's letter to John B.,<ptr target="n0129"/> &#38; suggested his sending
                it to O'Connor.<ptr target="n2002"/> Mrs Fairchild<ptr target="loc.02943_n2"/> asks
                affectionately after you. She is just going to England.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">W.S. Kennedy</signed>
            </closer>
